---
import Base from '../../layouts/Base.astro';
---
<Base title="NolteOS" description="The delivery operating system that powers predictable, forecast-based software delivery. Real-time visibility into every deliverable, decision, and metric — for you and your team." fullWidth>

  <!-- HERO -->
  <div class="os-hero">
    <div class="wide-wrap">
      <span class="os-eyebrow">The Delivery Operating System</span>
      <h1>Complete visibility into <em>every delivery</em></h1>
      <p class="os-hero-sub">NolteOS is how we manage your engagement — and how you stay in control of it. Real-time metrics, decision tracking, weekly delivery status, and async approvals. No status meetings required.</p>
      <div class="hero-actions">
        <a class="btn-hero btn-hero-primary" href="https://os.nolte.io">Get Your Delivery Plan</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- PRODUCT SHOT 1: PROJECT SNAPSHOT -->
  <div class="os-product-section">
    <div class="os-product-row">
      <div class="os-product-callout">
        <span class="os-callout-label">Project Snapshot</span>
        <h2>Know where your project stands — <em>always</em></h2>
        <p>Every engagement opens to a live snapshot: your active objective, engagement model, velocity, and key stakeholders. No digging through threads or waiting for a status call.</p>
        <ul class="os-callout-points">
          <li><strong>Active objective</strong> — the single goal your team is working toward, with a target date</li>
          <li><strong>Engagement model</strong> — your delivery velocity and what it covers</li>
          <li><strong>Stakeholders</strong> — who's involved, always visible</li>
        </ul>
        <span class="os-callout-why">Why it matters: You should never have to ask "what are we working on?" The answer is always on your dashboard.</span>
      </div>
      <div class="os-product-shot">
        <div class="shot-window">
          <div class="shot-toolbar">
            <span class="shot-dot"></span><span class="shot-dot"></span><span class="shot-dot"></span>
          </div>
          <div class="shot-content">
            <div class="shot-header-bar">
              <div class="shot-project-icon">N</div>
              <div>
                <div class="shot-project-name">Breeze Oral Care</div>
                <div class="shot-project-desc">HIPAA-compliant dental platform with clinical workflow integrations and patient portal.</div>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="shot-objective">
              <span class="shot-obj-label">Active Objective (Q2 2026)</span>
              <span class="shot-obj-text">Launch provider onboarding flow and insurance verification module by June 15, 2026</span>
            </div>
            <div class="shot-meta-row">
              <div class="shot-meta-item">
                <span class="shot-meta-label">Engagement</span>
                <span class="shot-meta-val">Velocity &mdash; 24 items/mo</span>
              </div>
              <div class="shot-meta-item">
                <span class="shot-meta-label">Stakeholders</span>
                <div class="shot-avatars">
                  <span class="shot-avatar">JT</span>
                  <span class="shot-avatar">JN</span>
                  <span class="shot-avatar">YL</span>
                  <span class="shot-avatar-more">+2</span>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- PRODUCT SHOT 2: DELIVERY METRICS -->
  <div class="os-product-section os-product-dark">
    <div class="os-product-row reverse">
      <div class="os-product-callout">
        <span class="os-callout-label">Delivery Metrics</span>
        <h2>Data that tells you if you're on track — <em>not opinions</em></h2>
        <p>Four numbers that matter. Updated in real time. Delivered this week, monthly progress against target, remaining items, and required weekly pace. When pace changes, you see it before it becomes a problem.</p>
        <ul class="os-callout-points">
          <li><strong>Weekly delivery count</strong> — what actually shipped, not what's "almost done"</li>
          <li><strong>Monthly progress</strong> — percentage against the forecasted target</li>
          <li><strong>Required pace</strong> — the math on what it takes to hit your timeline</li>
        </ul>
        <span class="os-callout-why">Why it matters: Forecasts mean nothing without accountability. These metrics are how we hold ourselves to the plan.</span>
      </div>
      <div class="os-product-shot">
        <div class="shot-window shot-window-dark">
          <div class="shot-toolbar">
            <span class="shot-dot"></span><span class="shot-dot"></span><span class="shot-dot"></span>
          </div>
          <div class="shot-content">
            <div class="shot-metrics-grid">
              <div class="shot-metric-card">
                <span class="shot-metric-label">Delivered This Week</span>
                <span class="shot-metric-val">10</span>
                <span class="shot-metric-trend positive">Up from 6 last week</span>
              </div>
              <div class="shot-metric-card">
                <span class="shot-metric-label">March Total</span>
                <span class="shot-metric-val">16 <span class="shot-metric-of">of 34</span></span>
                <span class="shot-metric-trend">47% of target</span>
              </div>
              <div class="shot-metric-card">
                <span class="shot-metric-label">Items Remaining</span>
                <span class="shot-metric-val">18</span>
                <span class="shot-metric-trend">2 weeks left in March</span>
              </div>
              <div class="shot-metric-card">
                <span class="shot-metric-label">Required Weekly Pace</span>
                <span class="shot-metric-val">9.0</span>
                <span class="shot-metric-trend positive">Down from 9.3</span>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="shot-progress">
              <div class="shot-progress-label">March Delivery Progress</div>
              <div class="shot-progress-bar">
                <div class="shot-progress-fill" style="width: 47%;"></div>
                <div class="shot-progress-marker" style="left: 50%;"></div>
              </div>
              <div class="shot-progress-legend">
                <span>47% delivered</span>
                <span class="shot-progress-expected">Expected: 50%</span>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- PRODUCT SHOT 3: KANBAN FLOW -->
  <div class="os-product-section">
    <div class="os-product-row">
      <div class="os-product-callout">
        <span class="os-callout-label">Kanban Flow</span>
        <h2>See every deliverable move through the <em>pipeline</em></h2>
        <p>Seven stages from specification to done. Click any stage to see every item in it. No ambiguity about where things are or what's blocking them. Flags surface immediately — blocked items, pending approvals, client dependencies.</p>
        <ul class="os-callout-points">
          <li><strong>7 clear stages</strong> — Awaiting Spec → In Spec → Ready → In Progress → Done Implementing → Validation → Done</li>
          <li><strong>Clickable stages</strong> — expand any column to see item details</li>
          <li><strong>Real-time flags</strong> — blocked items and pending approvals are visible at a glance</li>
        </ul>
        <span class="os-callout-why">Why it matters: You should be able to answer "where is my feature?" in under five seconds.</span>
      </div>
      <div class="os-product-shot">
        <div class="shot-window">
          <div class="shot-toolbar">
            <span class="shot-dot"></span><span class="shot-dot"></span><span class="shot-dot"></span>
          </div>
          <div class="shot-content">
            <div class="shot-kanban">
              <div class="shot-kanban-col">
                <div class="shot-kanban-header">Awaiting Spec<span class="shot-kanban-count">8</span></div>
                <div class="shot-kanban-card">Client Dashboard MVP</div>
                <div class="shot-kanban-card">Provider Search v2</div>
                <div class="shot-kanban-card faded">+6 more</div>
              </div>
              <div class="shot-kanban-col">
                <div class="shot-kanban-header">In Progress<span class="shot-kanban-count">3</span></div>
                <div class="shot-kanban-card">Insurance Verification</div>
                <div class="shot-kanban-card flagged">
                  AWS Migration
                  <span class="shot-flag blocked">Blocked</span>
                </div>
                <div class="shot-kanban-card">Auth Flow v2</div>
              </div>
              <div class="shot-kanban-col">
                <div class="shot-kanban-header">Validation<span class="shot-kanban-count">2</span></div>
                <div class="shot-kanban-card">Onboarding Wizard</div>
                <div class="shot-kanban-card flagged">
                  Dashboard Design
                  <span class="shot-flag pending">Pending Approval</span>
                </div>
              </div>
              <div class="shot-kanban-col done">
                <div class="shot-kanban-header">Done This Week<span class="shot-kanban-count">10</span></div>
                <div class="shot-kanban-card">Plan Calculator</div>
                <div class="shot-kanban-card">Lead Capture Flow</div>
                <div class="shot-kanban-card faded">+8 more</div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- PRODUCT SHOT 4: DECISIONS & APPROVALS -->
  <div class="os-product-section os-product-dark">
    <div class="os-product-row reverse">
      <div class="os-product-callout">
        <span class="os-callout-label">Decisions &amp; Approvals</span>
        <h2>Every decision recorded. Nothing <em>lost.</em></h2>
        <p>Meetings produce decisions and agreements. NolteOS captures them automatically — who decided what, when, and what action items came out of it. Pending approvals surface in your dashboard with due dates so you can act on your schedule.</p>
        <ul class="os-callout-points">
          <li><strong>Async approvals</strong> — approve directly from your dashboard, no meeting needed</li>
          <li><strong>Decision history</strong> — searchable record of every decision across every meeting</li>
          <li><strong>Action items</strong> — auto-generated from meeting transcripts, assigned and tracked</li>
        </ul>
        <span class="os-callout-why">Why it matters: "What did we decide?" is the most expensive question in software. You'll never need to ask it.</span>
      </div>
      <div class="os-product-shot">
        <div class="shot-window shot-window-dark">
          <div class="shot-toolbar">
            <span class="shot-dot"></span><span class="shot-dot"></span><span class="shot-dot"></span>
          </div>
          <div class="shot-content">
            <div class="shot-approvals">
              <div class="shot-approval-row">
                <div class="shot-approval-status approved">Approved</div>
                <div class="shot-approval-info">
                  <div class="shot-approval-title">Calculator — Shipped & Approved</div>
                  <div class="shot-approval-detail">All 7 stories delivered. Epic complete.</div>
                </div>
                <div class="shot-approval-date">Mar 14</div>
              </div>
              <div class="shot-approval-row">
                <div class="shot-approval-status approved">Approved</div>
                <div class="shot-approval-info">
                  <div class="shot-approval-title">Design Direction — Blue Palette</div>
                  <div class="shot-approval-detail">Approved in Feb 26 design review.</div>
                </div>
                <div class="shot-approval-date">Feb 26</div>
              </div>
              <div class="shot-approval-row highlight">
                <div class="shot-approval-status pending-status">Pending</div>
                <div class="shot-approval-info">
                  <div class="shot-approval-title">Client Dashboard Design</div>
                  <div class="shot-approval-detail">Approval needed to move 2 stories to ready.</div>
                </div>
                <div class="shot-approval-action">
                  <button class="shot-approve-btn">Approve</button>
                </div>
              </div>
              <div class="shot-approval-row highlight">
                <div class="shot-approval-status pending-status">Pending</div>
                <div class="shot-approval-info">
                  <div class="shot-approval-title">20% Bonus Capacity Model</div>
                  <div class="shot-approval-detail">Capacity benchmark complete. Due Mar 24.</div>
                </div>
                <div class="shot-approval-action">
                  <button class="shot-approve-btn">Approve</button>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- PRODUCT SHOT 5: MEETING INTELLIGENCE -->
  <div class="os-product-section">
    <div class="os-product-row">
      <div class="os-product-callout">
        <span class="os-callout-label">Meeting Intelligence</span>
        <h2>Meetings that produce <em>outcomes</em>, not confusion</h2>
        <p>Every meeting is transcribed and processed into structured decisions, agreements, and action items. Recaps are finalized and shareable. Work items are generated directly from what was agreed — no manual translation.</p>
        <ul class="os-callout-points">
          <li><strong>Structured recaps</strong> — decisions, agreements, and action items extracted automatically</li>
          <li><strong>Searchable history</strong> — find any decision from any meeting instantly</li>
          <li><strong>Work item generation</strong> — agreements become deliverables with one click</li>
        </ul>
        <span class="os-callout-why">Why it matters: The gap between "what we discussed" and "what we're building" is where most projects fail. NolteOS closes it.</span>
      </div>
      <div class="os-product-shot">
        <div class="shot-window">
          <div class="shot-toolbar">
            <span class="shot-dot"></span><span class="shot-dot"></span><span class="shot-dot"></span>
          </div>
          <div class="shot-content">
            <div class="shot-meeting">
              <div class="shot-meeting-header">
                <div class="shot-meeting-title">Weekly Delivery Meeting</div>
                <div class="shot-meeting-date">March 17, 2026</div>
              </div>
              <div class="shot-meeting-tags">
                <span class="shot-tag decisions">4 Decisions</span>
                <span class="shot-tag agreements">5 Agreements</span>
                <span class="shot-tag actions">5 Action Items</span>
              </div>
              <div class="shot-meeting-items">
                <div class="shot-decision-row">
                  <span class="shot-decision-icon">D</span>
                  <span>Use dashboard as client-facing view</span>
                </div>
                <div class="shot-decision-row">
                  <span class="shot-decision-icon">D</span>
                  <span>Apply design system globally</span>
                </div>
                <div class="shot-decision-row agreement">
                  <span class="shot-decision-icon a">A</span>
                  <span>Dashboard should be self-explanatory — no training needed</span>
                </div>
                <div class="shot-decision-row agreement">
                  <span class="shot-decision-icon a">A</span>
                  <span>Add "Expected Next Week" section with flags</span>
                </div>
              </div>
              <div class="shot-meeting-recap">
                <span class="shot-recap-badge">Recap Finalized</span>
                <span class="shot-recap-actions">Edit &middot; Share &middot; Generate Work Items</span>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- PRODUCT SHOT 6: WEEKLY DELIVERY STATUS -->
  <div class="os-product-section os-product-dark">
    <div class="os-product-row reverse">
      <div class="os-product-callout">
        <span class="os-callout-label">Weekly Delivery Status</span>
        <h2>What shipped. What's next. <em>What's flagged.</em></h2>
        <p>Every week, your dashboard shows exactly what was delivered, grouped by epic. Next to it: what's expected next week, with flags for anything blocked or waiting on you. This is the heartbeat of your engagement.</p>
        <ul class="os-callout-points">
          <li><strong>Delivered this week</strong> — grouped by epic, with item-level detail</li>
          <li><strong>Expected next week</strong> — what's coming, with blocker and approval flags</li>
          <li><strong>Weekly pace tracking</strong> — actual vs. target, updated in real time</li>
        </ul>
        <span class="os-callout-why">Why it matters: A weekly email summary is someone's interpretation. Your dashboard is the source of truth.</span>
      </div>
      <div class="os-product-shot">
        <div class="shot-window shot-window-dark">
          <div class="shot-toolbar">
            <span class="shot-dot"></span><span class="shot-dot"></span><span class="shot-dot"></span>
          </div>
          <div class="shot-content">
            <div class="shot-delivery-cols">
              <div class="shot-delivery-col">
                <div class="shot-delivery-heading">Delivered This Week <span class="shot-delivery-count">10</span></div>
                <div class="shot-epic-group">
                  <span class="shot-epic-name">Product Calculator</span>
                  <div class="shot-delivery-item done">&#10003; Structured Delivery Plan</div>
                  <div class="shot-delivery-item done">&#10003; Lead Capture Flow</div>
                  <div class="shot-delivery-item done">&#10003; Follow-Up Automations</div>
                  <div class="shot-delivery-item done">&#10003; Design Refinement</div>
                  <div class="shot-delivery-item faded">+3 more items</div>
                </div>
                <div class="shot-epic-group">
                  <span class="shot-epic-name">AI Infrastructure</span>
                  <div class="shot-delivery-item done">&#10003; Otto Agent E2E</div>
                  <div class="shot-delivery-item done">&#10003; Docker + GitHub PR</div>
                  <div class="shot-delivery-item done">&#10003; Slack Execution</div>
                </div>
              </div>
              <div class="shot-delivery-col">
                <div class="shot-delivery-heading">Expected Next Week <span class="shot-delivery-count">9</span></div>
                <div class="shot-delivery-item">Otto on AWS Fargate</div>
                <div class="shot-delivery-item flag-blocked">
                  <span>Provider API Integration</span>
                  <span class="shot-inline-flag blocked">Blocked</span>
                </div>
                <div class="shot-delivery-item">Dashboard MVP Build</div>
                <div class="shot-delivery-item flag-pending">
                  <span>Project Snapshot Surface</span>
                  <span class="shot-inline-flag pending">Pending Approval</span>
                </div>
                <div class="shot-delivery-item">Klipster AI Readiness</div>
                <div class="shot-delivery-item faded">+4 more items</div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- COMPARED TO -->
  <div class="os-contrast">
    <div class="wide-wrap">
      <h2 class="section-heading">What you get vs. <em>what you're used to</em></h2>
    </div>
    <div class="os-compare-grid">
      <div class="os-compare-col">
        <span class="os-compare-label old">Typical Agency</span>
        <ul>
          <li>Weekly status calls to learn what happened</li>
          <li>Jira board you have to interpret yourself</li>
          <li>Decisions lost in email and Slack threads</li>
          <li>Estimates that change every sprint</li>
          <li>"We're on track" with no supporting data</li>
          <li>Invoices based on hours, not outcomes</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="os-compare-col">
        <span class="os-compare-label new">With NolteOS</span>
        <ul>
          <li>Live dashboard — check anytime, no meetings needed</li>
          <li>Kanban flow with clear stages and item details</li>
          <li>Every decision recorded, searchable, and tracked</li>
          <li>Forecasts backed by three years of throughput data</li>
          <li>Weekly pace vs. target with variance tracking</li>
          <li>Fixed price per delivery — pay for what ships</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- TESTIMONIAL -->
  <div class="testimonial">
    <div class="testimonial-inner">
      <blockquote>They can build anything and do so beautifully and on time. They have also helped me tremendously in thinking strategically, even if it means I'm paying them less in the short term. They act like a partner in my business.</blockquote>
      <cite>Dr. Josh Turnbull &mdash; Founder, Breeze Oral Care</cite>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- CTA -->
  <div class="footer-cta">
    <div class="wide-wrap">
      <h2>See it for <em>yourself.</em></h2>
      <p>Describe what you're building. Get a predictable delivery plan with scope, timeline, and cost — powered by NolteOS.</p>
      <a class="btn-accent" href="https://os.nolte.io">Get Your Delivery Plan</a>
    </div>
  </div>

</Base>
